===Etymology===
From Japanese [[京]] (''kyō'', "capital") + [[都]] (''to'', "metropolis").

===Proper noun===
'''Kyoto'''

# A city in [[Japan]] on the island of [[Honshu]] that once served as Japan’s capital.
# The Kyoto [[protocol|Protocol]] to the [[United Nations]] Framework Convention on [[climate change|Climate Change]] -- An [[amendment]] to the [[international]] [[treaty]] on climate change, assigning [[mandatory]] targets for the [[reduction]] of [[greenhouse gas]] [[emission]]s to [[signatory]] [[nation]]s.

===Alternative spellings===
* [[Kioto]]

